results.description:
White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
Monk Parakeets Eating Acorns
I ran into a group of monk parakeets chowing down on the multitude of acorns on the ground under a live oak.  They were too busy eating to pay any attention to me so I was able to be close to them.  They were quite efficient using their feet to pick up and hold the acorns while they used their strong beaks to open and consume the acorns.  Acorns must be delicious, they were very enthusiastic about them. Once they broke the acorn open with their beak, they used their tongue to guide the meat down the gullet.
